/*!
  \page install_supportedos Supported Operating Systems
  PandA is developed and validated primarily on 64-bit Linux systems.

  This page intentionally avoids a frozen distro/version matrix: exact host distributions change over time more quickly than the documentation, while the practical requirement is a recent Linux environment with the tools needed by the selected build flow.

  The most stable choices are:
  - a recent Debian- or Ubuntu-based distribution;
  - a recent Red Hat, Rocky, AlmaLinux, or Fedora-derived distribution;
  - a containerized Linux environment built from the recipes shipped in the repository.

  \section install_supportedos_notes Notes
  Keep the following in mind:
  - CMake is the preferred build system for current development flows;
  - Autotools remains available for compatibility, but should not be treated as the default path for new instructions;
  - synthesis, simulation, and FPGA back-end flows may require additional vendor tools beyond the base host OS;
  - if host-package availability is a concern, prefer the container-based workflow described in \ref install_docker.

  Operating systems not listed above may still work, but they should be treated as best-effort configurations unless they are covered by current CI or actively maintained developer environments.

*/
